Detailed Description

A Uniform Resource Locator that identifies the location of an Internet resource.

To create a url to www.example.com 

 Url("www.example.com");

bool gaia::net::Url::isEmpty ( ) const

Returns true if the URL is zero-length.

Note that empty URLs are also invalid, and isValid() will return false for them. This is provided because some users may want to treat the empty case differently.

bool gaia::net::Url::isHostIPAddress ( ) const

Returns true if the hostname is an IP address.

Note: this function isn't as cheap as a simple getter because it re-parses the hostname to verify.

Returns:
true if hostname of this Url object is an IP address.
